title: ANyone recognize these Glyphs?
content:
Hey Y'all.  
Does anyone have an idea what font these glyphs are from?  
Looks like a million things, but can't identify it!  
Thanks

| Attachment | Size |
| --- | --- |
| [Capture.PNG](http://web.archive.org/web/20140715034719/http:/typophile.com/files/Capture_5.PNG) | 27.33 KB |
author: alfa60

comments.content: Some details reminds me of [Mercator](http://web.archive.org/web/20140715034719/http:/typophile.com/node/53257) but that's not it and none of its reinterpretation: [Atlas Grotesk](http://web.archive.org/web/20140715034719/http:/commercialtype.com/typefaces/atlas/grotesk), [Circular](http://web.archive.org/web/20140715034719/http:/lineto.com/The+Fonts/Font+Categories/Text+Fonts/Circular), [Founders Grotesk](http://web.archive.org/web/20140715034719/http:/typophile.com/wiki/https%3A/%252Fwww.klim.co.nz/retail-fonts/founders-grotesk). Where does this sample come from?

I also thought it might be Circular, but that R is weird...  
The sample was found online but the original source escapes me.  
Would just like to understand if its an actual font or just these glyphs.  
Thanks for your comment!

Hey y'all,  
I tried the what-the-font service to no avail.... any other guesses?
